          Maastricht Automatic Data Processing and Display System (MADAP) is the data centre of MUAC and provides data processing and display capabilities to these local operational services, and also remotely to the Belgian Air Force.
Within MUAC, the NETWORK Team is responsible for all LAN and WAN infrastructure and network IT security systems. It faces sustained high levels of workload due to a number of complex projects requiring LAN and/or WAN connectivity, activities aiming at the timely replacement of obsolete hence unsupported IT equipment. In addition, the drastic increase of home-users in 2020 has resulted in a number of technical and organisational measures to assure full access to all necessary on-site resources from any remote location without any compromise to security.
EUROCONTROL requires 2 full-time experts to assist the internal staff. These engineers will replace contractors or staff currently working in the NET Team. We are seeking two self-motivated individuals to take on the function of Senior Network Engineers who will be responsible and accountable for providing support for the systems in the team’s portfolio.
Skills, knowledge, experience required:
• A Bachelor’s Degree in engineering (computer science, electrical engineering, telecommunications) or equivalent;
• Minimum 5 years’ relevant experience in networking and IT security technology including practical experience in network troubleshooting on network equipment together with experience in the field of hardware installation, system integration, testing, and servicing activities;
• Cisco CCNP accredited;
• Practical experience with the following providers:
o Cisco;
o Check Point;
o Fortinet;
• Detailed knowledge of data communication protocols (TCP/IP, DNS, HTTP/S, FTP, etc.), routing, and switching, proven by minimum 2 practical cases as an example;
• Knowledge of quality of service (QoS) with experience in designing/implementing it in an enterprise environment proven by minimum 1 practical cases as an example;
• Familiarity with:
o Network management and security information and event management (SIEM) tools such as:
▪ Zenoss;
▪ DX Spectrum (formerly CA Spectrum);
▪ Splunk;
o Design concepts in LAN/WAN design;
• Experience with:
o Project environment;
o Quality/security standards;
o Configuration management and tools;
o Analysis and specs writing;
o Working in a multi-cultural team proven with at least one reference case;
• Good knowledge of MS Office tools including:
o MS Word;
o MS Excel;
o MS Visio;
• Ability to:
o Draft clear and concise technical papers in English;
o Communicate technical details clearly and succinctly to peers and to Management;
• Autonomy: ability to deliver quality output with minimum guidance;
• Motivation and commitment to deliver under tight time constraints;
• Good interpersonal and team-working skills;
• Result-driven, readiness to change, customer focus, integrity and team player approach;
• Multitasking and analytical skills;
• Very good oral and written communication skills in English (listening/reading/writing: C1/B2/B2).
Desirable:
• Practical experience with:
o Gigamon;
o Automation, particularly scripting, e.g. with Python;
o Network management systems;
• Well-familiarized with wireless products;
• Knowledge of Dutch and/or German.
Duties/role:
• Identifying malfunctioning hardware and/or software for the purpose of implementing necessary corrective actions, resolving technical problems and providing ongoing support to the end-users of the operational MADAP networks and non-operational OFFICE network;
• Performing primary network system administration on network and IT network security equipment;
• Providing assistance in design, development, configuration, installation, and maintenance of the network systems;
• Conducting analyses and testing of network systems for the purpose of documenting findings and ensuring efficiency;
• Creating utilities for the purpose of automating repetitive and daily routines;
• Implementing new network operating systems and application software for the purpose of ensuring compliance with licensing, patches, and updates according to vendor and/or IT security guidelines;
• Monitoring LAN/WAN infrastructure for the purpose of measuring performance and/or ensuring the secure and reliable operation of all MADAP networks and its network security infrastructure;
• Drafting TE2 documentation, e.g. build state documents, test documentation, version documentation, baseline documentation in accordance with the Maastricht Management System;
• Performing other related duties as assigned, for the purpose of ensuring the efficient and effective functioning of the NET Team




